      "id": "PopularPost126655",
      "post_content": "Remember, people, red gets tough creatures only for hilariously prohibitive costs.  \nThis is only 2 mana more than Hill Giant(I know, sorry), for flash, a +4/+0 buff on any creature, and a sturdy 3/4 that you can attack with your next combat step, should you play it on your opponent's turn.  \n  \nAnd don't forget that you can flash him in to block and have him block as a 7/4.  \n  \nOr why not, play him during your own combat step after blockers have been declared to one-up Giant Growth in terms of unblocked creature effectiveness.",
      "posted_by": "NoobOfLore",
