    {
      "id": "PopularPost354307",
      "post_content": "@syrazemyla: you raise a point that I've seen raised a lot on gatherer, which is that rarity shouldn't determine how good a card is. This is true... up to a point. As a dedicated limited player, changing a card's playability and rarity has a huge impact on how well the set drafts. If a really good card can be found at common, it warps the way you pick in draft, and can make the format less fun. I understand the cost concern when a card gets put at rare, but at the same time, imagine that it's possible to find a deck that has two (or even more) of a specific rare. People who think that card quality shouldn't increase with rarity at all don't understand the nuance of creating a fun limited environment.  \n  \nOh right, the card:  \n  \nmost purely power-boosting combat tricks don't allow your target to survive combat. This means two things for this card:  \n-you can one-for-one as a surprise blocker, which is alright  \n-you still get a card out of the deal after using the pump effect to kill something.  \n  \n... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Aremath",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost354307\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_post\">@syrazemyla: you raise a point that I've seen raised a lot on gatherer, which is that rarity shouldn't determine how good a card is. This is true... up to a point. As a dedicated limited player, changing a card's playability and rarity has a huge impact on how well the set drafts. If a really good card can be found at common, it warps the way you pick in draft, and can make the format less fun. I understand the cost concern when a card gets put at rare, but at the same time, imagine that it's possible to find a deck that has two (or even more) of a specific rare. People who think that card quality shouldn't increase with rarity at all don't understand the nuance of creating a fun limited environment.<br/><br/>Oh right, the card:<br/><br/>most purely power-boosting combat tricks don't allow your target to survive combat. This means two things for this card:<br/>-you can one-for-one as a surprise blocker, which is alright<br/>-you still get a card out of the deal after using the pump effect to kill something.<br/><br/>... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 354307)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '354307'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n